[0.007, "o", "# Bug: Test Issue 5\r\n\r\n## Objective:\r\nCreate a minimal, reproducible test case and ensure the test-related helper functions handle test issue creation correctly; if the issue is due to a missing validation or incorrect handling of test-issue data, add proper validation and update the code paths that create or render issue test data.\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce:\r\n- Use the repository's issue creation flow (or GitHub CLI) to create a test issue with a short body: \"Creating a test issue for my issues to md eval.\" and verify it appears in the issue list output.\r\n- Run the command used by integrations (e.g., the script or gh CLI command) to list issues and confirm the created issue appears with correct title, number, body, and timestamps.\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria:\r\n- The created test issue appears in the repository issue list with the exact title \"Test Issue\" and body \"Creating a test issue for my issues to md eval.\".\r\n- The issue listing command returns the issue with correct JSON fields: title, body, number, state"]
[0.000, "o", ", createdAt, and updatedAt.\r\n- Any bug in parsing or displaying test issue data is fixed so downstream tools (scripts or templates) can consume the issue fields without errors.\r\n"]
